==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bitumen
<hw>Bi*tu"men</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>bitumen</ets>: cf. F. <ets>bitume</ets>. Cf.
<er>B⟦eacute⟧ton</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Mineral pitch; a black,
tarry substance, burning with a bright flame; Jew's pitch. It occurs as
an abundant natural product in many places, as on the shores of the Dead
and Caspian Seas. It is used in cements, in the construction of
pavements, etc. See <er>Asphalt</er>. </def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 150 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>By extension, any one of the natural hydrocarbons,
including the hard, solid, brittle varieties called asphalt, the
semisolid maltha and mineral tars, the oily petroleums, and even the
light, volatile naphthas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bitumen process</ent>⟦br⟧
